    <!-- OVERVIEW -->
    <section id="overview" class="section section-anchor">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>
        This app walks you through a <strong>4.44 kg</strong> bone-in standing rib roast with garlic mashed potatoes, pan jus, and horseradish cream for an on-time <span class="highlight">5:00 PM dinner</span> with guests arriving around <span class="highlight">4:00–4:30 PM</span>. [web:27][web:30][page:1]
      </p>
      <div class="two-column">
        <div>
          <h3>Specs</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Meat: 4.44 kg bone-in standing rib roast (prime rib). [web:27]</li>
            <li>Portions: ~8 generous servings plus leftovers. [web:27][web:30]</li>
            <li>Method: Low-and-slow to 118°F / 47°C, long rest, then hot reverse sear at 500°F / 260°C. [page:1]</li>
            <li>Target doneness: Medium-rare center, warmer edges. [page:1]</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Equipment</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Large roasting pan or deep sheet tray.</li>
            <li>Wire rack (optional if using bones + herb bed). [page:1]</li>
            <li>Probe or instant-read thermometer (non-negotiable). [page:1]</li>
            <li>Stovetop-safe pan for jus.</li>
            <li>Large pot and masher/ricer for potatoes. [web:15]</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="note">
        Heavy lifting is done the day before and early afternoon; from about 4 PM you are mostly finishing crust, carving, and plating. [page:1]
      </p>
    </section>

